comment: /**  * To use a specific {@link io.micrometer.core.instrument.MeterRegistry} instance.  * <p/>  * If no instance has been configured, then Camel will create a shared instance to be used.  */
code: /**  * To use a specific {@link io.micrometer.core.instrument.MeterRegistry} instance.  * <p/>  * If no instance has been configured, then Camel will create a shared instance to be used.  */ public void setMeterRegistry(MeterRegistry meterRegistry) {     this.meterRegistry = meterRegistry. }

comment: /**  * Whether to use pretty print when outputting JSon  */
code: /**  * Whether to use pretty print when outputting JSon  */ public void setPrettyPrint(boolean prettyPrint) {     this.prettyPrint = prettyPrint. }

comment: /**  * Sets the time unit to use for requests per unit (eg requests per second)  */
code: /**  * Sets the time unit to use for requests per unit (eg requests per second)  */ public TimeUnit getDurationUnit() {     return durationUnit. }

comment: /**  * Sets the time unit to use for timing the duration of processing a message in the route  */
code: /**  * Sets the time unit to use for timing the duration of processing a message in the route  */ public void setDurationUnit(TimeUnit durationUnit) {     this.durationUnit = durationUnit. }

@Override public RoutePolicy createRoutePolicy(CamelContext camelContext, String routeId, NamedNode routeDefinition) {     MicrometerRoutePolicy answer = new MicrometerRoutePolicy().     answer.setMeterRegistry(getMeterRegistry()).     answer.setPrettyPrint(isPrettyPrint()).     answer.setDurationUnit(getDurationUnit()).     answer.setNamingStrategy(getNamingStrategy()).     return answer. }
